title: For Sale/Trade:  Winchester 1893
postcontent: Fairly hard to come by Winchester Model 1893. The pre-cursor to the Model 1897 they were only produced for three years between 1893 and 1896. Approximately 34,000 total. They are black powder only. Winchester offered a voluntary trade in program for a new Model 1897 when it was introduced. This particular 1893 was manufactured in 1895. It has typical handling marks for a 120 year old gun but everything works as it should and the bore is in excellent shape. The fore end is not cracked, a common problem for the early, three-screw style fore ends. It is missing the butt plate. It had a rubber Pachmyr pad on it when I got it, but it looked terrible so I took it off. An early 1897 plate should be an accurate replacement. It has a somewhat strange patina too it, I have no explanation for it.I'm interested in trades for other early and antique sporting arms and curiosa. I am not really interested in Mil-surps, maybe US military.  I will trade up or down with cash either way.  Face to Face sale only and I might ask to see ID or a LTCF.
